author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
President Donald Trump won Arizona in November, but Democratic Senator Ruben Gallego also captured the state. The Wall Street Journal sat down with him to learn how he held on to voters Kamala Harris lost, and where the party goes from here.

Gallego also discusses what voters care about the most including national security, the economy, immigration and tariffs.
